title: Aftershocks jar northern California
paragraphs: A 3.4-magnitude earthquake rumbled through northern California early Sunday, the U.S. Geological Survey said.
One was a 3.9 magnitude aftershock that struck near American Canyon.
It was the largest since the 6.0 quake hit in the same area early Sunday.
Dozens of people were injured in Sundayâ€™s quake, which caused at least $1 billion in property damage in Napa and other communities.
